body:
To be more specific, during installation I got lots of warnings and messages like this:
```
    In file included from /usr/include/python3.4m/pyport.h:328:0,
                     from /usr/include/python3.4m/Python.h:50,
                     from numpy/core/src/umath/scalarmath.c.src:12:
    /usr/include/arm-linux-gnueabihf/bits/mathcalls.h:115:1: note: expected ‘long double *’ but argument is of type ‘npy_longdouble *’
     __MATHCALL (modf,, (_Mdouble_ __x, _Mdouble_ *__iptr)) __nonnull ((2));
     ^
    arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc: numpy/core/src/umath/umathmodule.c
```
or
```
     int casinhl (void);
         ^
    _configtest.c:2:5: warning: conflicting types for built-in function ‘casinl’
```
